                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1005">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Lee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Havana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-16T12:30:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1898—12.30 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi> blown up and destroyed to-night at 9.40 p.m.
                    Explosion occurred well forward under quarters of crew; consequence many were
                    lost. It is believed all officers saved, but Jenkins and Merritt not yet
                    accounted for. Cause of explosion yet to be investigated. Captain-General and
                    Spanish army and navy officers have rendered every assistance. Sigsbee and most
                    of his officers on Ward steamer <hi rend="italic">City of Washington</hi>.
                    Others on Spanish man-of-war and in city. Am with Sigsbee now, who has
                    telegraphed Navy Department.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
